[{'text': '[SciShow Intro]', 'start': 0.0, 'duration': 1.12}, {'text': 'You frequent flyer types are probably used to it,', 'start': 4.86, 'duration': 1.54}, {'text': 'but the fact is, when we travel by air,', 'start': 6.4, 'duration': 1.44}, {'text': 'we are way up there.', 'start': 7.98, 'duration': 1.42}, {'text': 'The average cruising altitude of a commercial jet is', 'start': 9.46, 'duration': 2.12}, {'text': '7 1/2 to 11 kilometers.', 'start': 11.58, 'duration': 2.2}, {'text': 'In horizontal terms, that is at least as far as the average distance', 'start': 13.78, 'duration': 2.88}, {'text': 'between you and the nearest Starbucks at any given moment.', 'start': 16.78, 'duration': 3.16}, {'text': "In vertical terms, well, that's a long way down.", 'start': 19.94, 'duration': 2.64}, {'text': 'The good news is that the place starts to fall and has a long time to figure out how to stop falling.', 'start': 22.58, 'duration': 4.5}, {'text': "But we've been flying that high ever since the development of the jet engine in the mid-1950s.", 'start': 27.08, 'duration': 4.78}, {'text': "And jets were designed to fly at these high altitudes because there's less air up there.", 'start': 31.86, 'duration': 4.96}, {'text': "And that's what engineers, 
passengers, and airlines all prefer.", 'start': 36.82, 'duration': 3.5}, {'text': 'Basically, there are far fewer air molecules at say 30,000 feet or 9 kilometers than at sea level,', 'start': 40.32, 'duration': 5.96}, {'text': 'so the plane is literally running into fewer molecules.', 'start': 46.28, 'duration': 2.62}, {'text': "This means it doesn't have to produce as much thrust in order to maintain the speed necessary to fly.", 'start': 48.9, 'duration': 4.54}, {'text': 'So it can travel more efficiently, which is what the airlines want.', 'start': 53.44, 'duration': 3.02}, {'text': "What the passengers want is to not feel
like they're flying in the air at all,", 'start': 56.46, 'duration': 3.88}, {'text': 'and flying at higher altitudes means', 'start': 60.34, 'duration': 1.78}, {'text': 'being able to fly over at least some
of the weather patterns and air currents', 'start': 62.12, 'duration': 3.88}, {'text': 'that older, less powerful propeller planes
often had to fly through.', 'start': 66.0, 'duration': 3.78}, {'text': 'So flying higher usually means a more comfortable flight.', 'start': 69.78, 'duration': 2.96}, {'text': 'But there are some trade-offs
for this efficiency and comfort.', 'start': 72.74, 'duration': 2.4}, {'text': 'In order to stay in the air, an airplane needs to maintain lift, the force that counteracts its weight.', 'start': 75.14, 'duration': 4.9}, {'text': 'At lower altitudes, having lots of air around
helps a plane get lift,', 'start': 80.04, 'duration': 3.78}, {'text': 'but the higher it goes, the harder it is to maintain.', 'start': 83.82, 'duration': 2.22}, {'text': 'So engineers have to find ways to generate more lift in other ways, like making planes with larger wings.', 'start': 86.04, 'duration': 5.18}, {'text': "Jets can't fly too high, though.", 'start': 91.22, 'duration': 2.08}, {'text': 'In order to like continue working, jet engines need to burn fuel.', 'start': 93.3, 'duration': 2.9}, {'text': 'That is an important part of the process, and to burn stuff, you need oxygen.', 'start': 96.2, 'duration': 3.58}, {'text': "So planes have to stay at altitudes where there's still enough oxygen to mix with the jet fuel,", 'start': 99.78, 'duration': 3.98}, {'text': 'and allow combustion to happen.', 'start': 103.76, 'duration': 1.62}, {'text': 'To get any higher, your aircraft would have to pack canisters of air to mix with the fuel,', 'start': 105.38, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': "and once you do that, you're not an airplane anymore; you're basically a rocket.", 'start': 109.4, 'duration': 3.58}, {'text': 'So engineers have done the math and found the optimal height for efficient travel,', 'start': 112.98, 'duration': 3.92}, {'text': 'and designed planes to operate best at that height.', 'start': 116.9, 'duration': 3.06}, {'text': 'Yay engineers!', 'start': 119.96, 'duration': 0.84}, {'text': 'Thanks to our friends on tumblr who asked this question.', 'start': 120.8, 'duration': 1.94}, {'text': 'Thank you to our Patreon patrons who keep these answers coming.', 'start': 122.74, 'duration': 2.78}, {'text': "If you'd like to submit questions to be answered, or get these quick questions a few days before", 'start': 125.52, 'duration': 4.08}, {'text': 'everyone else, you can go to patreon.com/scishow', 'start': 129.6, 'duration': 2.2}, {'text': '[SciShow Outro]', 'start': 131.8, 'duration': 8.46}]
